  "text": "Piezoceramics are often used in atomic force microscopy (AFM) as nano-positioning actuators to drive the scanning probes because of their high resolution and fast response [CITATION_1] . However, the inherent hysteresis (see Fig. 1 ) of a piezoceramic actuator may lead to AFM imaging distortion (see Fig. 2 ).",
